Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Telos Group is one of the nation’s premier performance-oriented management and technology consulting firms.  Utilizing senior, experienced consultants, the firm specializes in blending the use of technology into modern business environments to improve overall performance, achieve competitive advantage, create a customer-centric culture, and streamline operational and financial performance.  The firm created and utilizes today’s leading enterprise/business performance management (EPM/BPM/CPM) methodology, The Performance Power Grid©, which has won awards for its ability to focus the utilization of technology upon the core needs of an organization.  The Telos Group's role in the marketplace differentiates them in several important ways: They offer full life-cycle services in their areas of focus. This includes the ability to communicate effectively with C-level executives, management and staff at all levels during both business and technology discussions, providing all necessary services and support during the visioning, planning, implementation and support phases of engagements.  The Telos Group possess a significant amount of practical experience creating and implementing initiatives that incorporate the use of technology to meet core business needs, utilizing a time-tested, award-winning methodology that compliments and improves the return on leading performance-oriented technologies and methodologies such as the Balanced Scorecard, APQC, Six Sigma, and Malcolm Baldrige.  The Telos Group has their own in-house staff of both business and technical consultants, allowing them to analyze problems from both a technology and business process perspective, creating a comprehensive implementation strategy and then, if desired, bring this vision to life.  The Telos Group has a close working relationship with – and are fully trained on – many of the technologies fulfilling needs in this area, including industry-leading tools by IBM, Oracle, Microsoft, SAP, Actuate and others.  As a “tool-agnostic” firm fully trained on most of today’s leading EPM technologies The Telos Group will be able to objectively identify the technology that best meets your specific needs, and apply it to effectively assist you in creating sustainable superior performance within your organization.  The Telos Group is also pleased to announce for the second time that a Telos client has now won the prestigious Business Finance Magazine Performance Management Vision Award. This award is given to only one organization in each of three categories per year.  Seattle City Light now joins their client FujiFilm USA as being recognized for utilizing an innovative and best practice approach to blending technology, process and information to drive overall performance.

Description: OpenRuns is the world's #1 app for pickup basketball!
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The world’s #1 pickup basketball app! OpenRuns is a social networking platform that brings hoopers together from around the world for the common purpose of finding places to play and meeting new players in your area. Whether it’s to organize runs, manage your pickup groups, share basketball content, or simply talk hoops - OpenRuns creates a tighter knit, global basketball community! Here’s a brief rundown of the app’s primary features: Newsfeed • The newsfeed uses geolocation to let you chat and interact with hoopers in your area. Think of it as a location based version of your Twitter timeline, but exclusively for hoops. Simply tap the pencil icon in the top right corner to create your own post or share photos. You can also like, comment, or upvote the best responses from other posts to join in the conversation. Overall, the newsfeed is great for sharing content, discussing hoops, or simply organizing runs via word of mouth! Nearby Runs • The nearby runs feed compiles a list of all the pickup games scheduled in your area. The feed allows you to create, search, and join games based on location, date, and skill level. Simply tap the orange basketball icon in the footer to create your own game. You then have the ability to choose a location, select a day/time, apply various privacy settings, tailor the game specifically to your desired level of experience, leave notes for game participants, and invite your friends!  Groups • Organizing your weekly runs via text messaging or email threads is now a thing of the past, as the groups feature provides you with the tools to easily and effectively manage your regularly scheduled pickup groups. To get started simply choose a name, select a privacy setting, and invite group members. Once created, each group has its own private newsfeed and pickup schedule. And the best part is that whenever there’s new group activity, every group member instantly receives a notification update! Ultimately, if you’re a hooper and love playing, OpenRuns is your go-to app for all things basketball related!

Description: Birthdays and virtual gifts on Twitter
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: TwellWishes is a Twitter app that allows Twitter users to send well wishes to their followers for birthdays, anniversaries, promotions, or whatever users would like. TwellWishes also doubles as a reminder service so that no one's birthday is ever forgotten.  Every user is given a link to share with their followers which allows people to add themselves to that user's birthday list.  When a birthday comes up, everyone with that birthday on their list will be reminded with one simple tweet.  They can send a tweet to that person from within TwellWishes or they can send a virtual gift such as a cake or a comfy pair of slippers. The idea came about after noticing there was no way to keep track of followers' birthdays.  Facebook users get that information automatically, but on Twitter users are only likely to know of another user's birthday either from seeing others tweeting about a birthday or if they actually know that person offline.  Furthermore, people usually end up with some kind of gift for their birthday, so TwellWishes includes a virtual gift store.  Users can send gifts with either credits or cash (via PayPal).  Everyone is given 100 gift credits upon signup to send at least one free gift.  When users run out of credits, they can easily purchase more.  Also, users can earn gift credits when they send gifts with cash via PayPal.

Description: Strayform is a Texas startup that, like SellaBand, Snocap and Amie Street , is giving unsigned artists a way to promote and sell their
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Strayform  is a Texas startup that, like [SellaBand](http://crunchbase.com/organization/sellaband), [Snocap](http://crunchbase.com/organization/snocap) and [Amie Street](http://crunchbase.com/organization/amiestreet) , is giving unsigned artists a way to promote and sell their music. Strayform is a community of artists and fans alike who are exposing the long tail of music through a reverse process.  Flipping the traditional model where music is made and then sold piece by piece, artists give away music in hopes that fans will support their future efforts.  Like SellaBand, artists sign up, upload some of their music and then create proposals for new music they want to create. Fans can listen to and download the music (DRM free), and donate directly to proposals they like. The proposals are all different. One artist, for example, says he will mention the name of person who pledges the most in the song itself. All music is Creative Commons licensed meaning fans are able to freely share their downloads on P2P networks. Strayform has had little press, but, inexplicably were covered by Fox News in a 3 minute segment. The video is available on their home page.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio

Description: Diversified Language Institute is a school in Los Angeles.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: While many vocational schools offer English as a Second Language classes, Diversified Language Institute makes ESL its primary focus. The institute offers academics specifically designed for international students, and is legally authorized to teach nonimmigrant students. Diversified Language Institute currently offers the following programs:   * English as a Second Language   * Business Office Administration   * Vocational English as a Second Language The ESL program is a 720-hour course that teaches practical English. Equal emphasis is place on speaking, listening, reading and writing, so you’ll have the language skills you need to enter the workplace or further your education. If you’re looking for career training, the Business Office Administration program might be a good option. This 720-hour course teaches the technical skills required for the office environment, while also improving your command of the English language. The Vocational English as a Second Language program is a 1080-hour course that combines aspects of the Business Office Administration and ESL courses. In Vocational ESL, you’ll study English for 360 hours, then continue to the Business Office Administration program. Description: Germfalcon is the first practical method for airplane cabin disinfection.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The GermFalcon is a patented sanitizing device that instantly kills infectious germs on surfaces and in surrounding air. Using only ultraviolet-C (UVC) light, the kind used in hospitals, this highly-effective device is mobile and compact — no larger than a flight attendant’s food and beverage cart. Designed to easily navigate an airplane cabin, the GermFalcon’s strategically placed UVC lamps expose seats and seatbacks, arm rests, tray tables, overhead bins, air and media controls, and floors to the germicidal effects of UVC rays. Harmful bacteria and viruses are instantly killed — even in the surrounding air. The GermFalcon’s design makes it user-friendly and operates in three important modes. In the cabin, both wings extend to efficiently treat the entire seating area. In the lavatory, a single extended wing reaches in to treat the sink, countertop and toilet. In the galley, both wings retract aiming the GermFalcon’s UVC lamps at countertops and crew area. The GermFalcon is battery-powered and can sanitize a plane in a matter of minutes. There is minimal labor cost, and no need for messy, toxic, ineffective chemical disinfectants.
